populateTree

void populateTree(org.eclipse.swt.widgets.TreeItem node,
                  java.lang.String parentName,
                  RationaleElementType type,
                  boolean firstTime)
Populates the rationale elements from the rationale database. This is a recursive method that calls itself to add new children to the current root node.

Parameters:
node - - the root node for the tree
parentName - - the name of the parent at the root node.
type - specify which type of element we should display as treeview.
firstTime - flag for whether this is the first time to call this method.
